---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ScrollReveal from '../components/ScrollReveal.astro';
import ComparisonBar from '../components/ComparisonBar.astro';
import TrustCertificate from '../components/TrustCertificate.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Tom Pickup"
  description="About Tom Pickup, Lancashire County Councillor for Padiham and Burnley West. Lead Member for Finance and Resources. Reform UK."
>
  <!-- Section 1: Page Header -->
  <section class="page-header-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="gradient-text">About Me</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Lancashire County Councillor for Padiham and Burnley West. Lead Member for Finance and Resources.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Bio -->
  <section class="bio-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="bio-grid">
          <div class="bio-photo">
            <img src="/images/headshot.jpg" alt="Tom Pickup, Lancashire County Councillor for Padiham and Burnley West" class="headshot" loading="eager" />
          </div>

          <div class="bio-text">
            <h2>Tom Pickup</h2>
            <div class="bio-meta">
              <span class="badge badge-teal">Reform UK</span>
              <span class="badge badge-teal">Padiham &amp; Burnley West</span>
              <span class="badge badge-teal">Lead Member for Finance &amp; Resources</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              I grew up in this area and I care deeply about its future. Like many residents, I watched
              council tax bills climb year after year while potholes multiplied, bins got missed, and the
              answers from County Hall never quite added up. I decided to stop complaining and start doing
              something about it.
            </p>
            <p>
              In May 2025, Lancashire voted for change &mdash; decisively. Reform won 53 of 84 seats,
              the largest majority any party has held at County Hall. As Lead Member for Finance and
              Resources, I inherited a &pound;28 million overspend, &pound;350 million in concealed bond
              losses, and a savings programme that had collapsed from 91% delivery to just 48%.
              We&rsquo;ve turned it around &mdash; the lowest council tax rise in 12 years, a balanced
              budget, and all five care homes saved.
            </p>
            <p>
              I was elected in 2025 on a Reform UK ticket, standing on a simple promise: transparency,
              accountability, and putting residents first. I don't do politics-as-usual. I ask the
              awkward questions, I dig into the numbers, and I publish what I find — because the people
              paying the bills have a right to know where their money goes.
            </p>
            <p>
              When I'm not at County Hall or in committee meetings, you'll find me out in the community
              talking to the people I represent. My door is always open, and I'm always happy to hear from
              residents of Padiham and Burnley West.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Timeline -->
  <section class="timeline-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Key Milestones</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">2025</span>
              <h3>Elected to Lancashire County Council</h3>
              <p>
                Won the Padiham and Burnley West division for Reform UK, joining the largest
                Reform group on any county council in England with 53 seats.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">2025</span>
              <h3>Appointed Lead Member for Finance &amp; Resources</h3>
              <p>
                Appointed to the cabinet as Lead Member for Finance and Resources at Lancashire
                County Council, overseeing the council's &pound;986 million budget and financial strategy.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">2025</span>
              <h3>Launched Councillor Website</h3>
              <p>
                Built this website to provide a direct, transparent line of communication
                between me and the residents I represent. No spin, no jargon.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">2026</span>
              <h3>Delivered Reform&rsquo;s First Budget</h3>
              <p>
                Balanced a &pound;1.33 billion budget with the lowest council tax rise in
                12 years (3.80%). Identified &pound;62 million in savings and corrected a
                &pound;28 million inherited overspend &mdash; all without cutting front-line services.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">2025</span>
              <h3>Saved All Five Care Homes</h3>
              <p>
                Inherited a Conservative consultation to close five county care homes. Listened
                to over 1,600 residents and reversed course &mdash; keeping all five open with
                new investment pledged.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">Ongoing</span>
              <h3>Community Engagement</h3>
              <p>
                Committed to holding regular surgeries and being available to residents.
                Your concerns drive my work at County Hall — from road repairs to planning
                issues to scrutinising budgets.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: What I've Achieved -->
  <section class="achievements-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">What I&rsquo;ve Achieved</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="achievements-grid stagger-children">
          <div class="achievement-card card">
            <span class="achievement-number" style="color: #30d158;">3.80%</span>
            <h3>Lowest CT Rise in 12 Years</h3>
            <p>The Conservatives raised council tax to the maximum in 7 of 8 years. Reform&rsquo;s first budget broke that pattern &mdash; saving households &pound;17.55 each versus the Tory approach.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="achievement-card card">
            <span class="achievement-number" style="color: #ff453a;">&pound;28M&rarr;&pound;6M</span>
            <h3>Inherited Overspend Corrected</h3>
            <p>We inherited a &pound;28 million overspend forecast. Through targeted action &mdash; not cuts to front-line services &mdash; we&rsquo;ve reduced it to &pound;6.1 million and falling.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="achievement-card card">
            <span class="achievement-number" style="color: var(--accent);">5</span>
            <h3>Care Homes Saved</h3>
            <p>Inherited a consultation to close them. Listened to 1,600+ residents. Kept all five open with new investment pledged &mdash; because elderly care isn&rsquo;t a line to cut.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="achievement-card card">
            <span class="achievement-number" style="color: #ff9f0a;">&pound;986M</span>
            <h3>Budget Oversight</h3>
            <p>As Lead Member for Finance &amp; Resources, overseeing Lancashire County Council&rsquo;s entire annual budget on behalf of residents.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="achievement-card card">
            <span class="achievement-number" style="color: #bf5af2;">&pound;18,000</span>
            <h3>Awarded to Burnley Arts</h3>
            <p>As Chairman of the Advisory Committee of the charity, distributed grants to 15 local arts organisations serving the community.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Political Priorities -->
  <section class="political-priorities-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">My Priorities</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="priorities-grid stagger-children">
          <div class="priority-static card">
            <div class="priority-static-icon" style="color: var(--accent);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M1 12s4-8 11-8 11 8 11 8-4 8-11 8-11-8-11-8z"></path>
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"></circle>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Radical Transparency</h3>
            <p>
              Open data, public scrutiny, and no backroom deals. Every council decision should be
              visible to the people who pay for it. I publish my findings, share the data, and
              invite challenge.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="priority-static card">
            <div class="priority-static-icon" style="color: var(--accent-green);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Accountable Governance</h3>
            <p>
              Councillors and officers should answer to residents, not the other way round.
              I challenge complacency, question spending decisions, and hold the executive
              to account in every meeting.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="priority-static card">
            <div class="priority-static-icon" style="color: var(--accent-orange);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"></polyline>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Data-Driven Decisions</h3>
            <p>
              Gut feeling and party loyalty shouldn't drive council policy. I use real data
              to understand problems, measure performance, and propose solutions. The numbers
              don't lie.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="priority-static card">
            <div class="priority-static-icon" style="color: var(--accent-purple);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path>
                <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle>
                <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path>
                <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Residents First</h3>
            <p>
              Every decision I make starts with one question: is this good for the people of
              Padiham and Burnley West? I'm not here for a career in politics. I'm here to
              serve my community.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Reform at LCC -->
  <section class="transparency-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Reform at Lancashire County Council</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="transparency-content">
          <p>
            When the Conservatives left County Hall, they left behind a mess: a &pound;28 million
            overspend, savings delivery that had collapsed from 91% to 48%, council tax raised to
            the legal maximum in 7 of 8 years, and &pound;350 million in bond losses they never
            transparently reported.
          </p>
          <p>
            In less than a year, Reform has delivered the lowest council tax rise in 12 years,
            identified &pound;62 million in savings, corrected the inherited overspend, saved all five
            county care homes, and stopped councillors collecting salaries for pension fund
            directorships. The 2026/27 budget is balanced at &pound;1.33 billion &mdash; without
            cutting front-line services.
          </p>

          <div class="about-comparisons">
            <ComparisonBar
              title="Council Tax Rise"
              reformValue="3.80%"
              reformPercent={63}
              conValue="4.99%"
              conPercent={83}
              lowerIsBetter={true}
              annotation="Reform delivered the lowest council tax rise in 12 years"
            />
            <ComparisonBar
              title="Savings Delivery Rate"
              reformValue="90%+"
              reformPercent={90}
              conValue="48%"
              conPercent={48}
              annotation="Conservative savings delivery collapsed over 8 years"
            />
          </div>

          <p>
            This is what happens when you put people who care about value for money in charge of
            the public purse. Lancashire voted for change &mdash; and change is being delivered.
          </p>

          <div class="about-trust">
            <TrustCertificate />
          </div>

          <div class="transparency-links">
            <a href="/news/" class="btn-primary">
              Read the Full Story
            </a>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn-secondary">Get in Touch</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: Accessibility Statement -->
  <section class="accessibility-section" id="accessibility">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="accessibility-card card">
          <h2>Accessibility Statement</h2>
          <p>
            This website aims to be accessible to as many people as possible, in line with
            <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong> guidelines. The site is built with semantic HTML,
            supports keyboard navigation, provides sufficient colour contrast, and respects user
            preferences for reduced motion.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you encounter any accessibility issues or have suggestions for improvement,
            please <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>. I take accessibility seriously and
            will work to resolve any barriers as quickly as possible.
          </p>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ---- Page Header ---- */
  .page-header-section {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .page-header-section h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  /* ---- Bio Section ---- */
  .bio-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .bio-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .bio-photo {
    width: 300px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .headshot {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .bio-text h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .bio-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .bio-text p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .bio-text p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Timeline ---- */
  .timeline-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 32px;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 11px;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      var(--accent) 0%,
      var(--accent-border) 30%,
      var(--border-color) 100%
    );
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  .timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .timeline-item:last-child {
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .timeline-dot {
    position: absolute;
    left: -32px;
    top: var(--space-lg);
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent);
    z-index: 1;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .timeline-dot::after {
    content: '';
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
  }

  .timeline-card {
    margin-left: var(--space-md);
  }

  .timeline-date {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  .timeline-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .timeline-card p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Stagger timeline animation */
  .timeline-item:nth-child(1) { opacity: 0; animation: fadeInUp 0.5s var(--ease-smooth) 0.1s forwards; }
  .timeline-item:nth-child(2) { opacity: 0; animation: fadeInUp 0.5s var(--ease-smooth) 0.2s forwards; }
  .timeline-item:nth-child(3) { opacity: 0; animation: fadeInUp 0.5s var(--ease-smooth) 0.3s forwards; }
  .timeline-item:nth-child(4) { opacity: 0; animation: fadeInUp 0.5s var(--ease-smooth) 0.4s forwards; }
  .timeline-item:nth-child(5) { opacity: 0; animation: fadeInUp 0.5s var(--ease-smooth) 0.5s forwards; }
  .timeline-item:nth-child(6) { opacity: 0; animation: fadeInUp 0.5s var(--ease-smooth) 0.6s forwards; }

  /* ---- Achievements ---- */
  .achievements-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .achievements-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .achievement-card {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .achievement-number {
    display: block;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  .achievement-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .achievement-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Political Priorities ---- */
  .political-priorities-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .priorities-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .priority-static {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .priority-static-icon {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    transition: transform var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .priority-static:hover .priority-static-icon {
    transform: scale(1.08) rotate(-3deg);
  }

  .priority-static h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .priority-static p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Transparency Section ---- */
  .transparency-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .transparency-content {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .transparency-content p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about-comparisons {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .about-trust {
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .transparency-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  /* ---- Accessibility Section ---- */
  .accessibility-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .accessibility-card {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .accessibility-card h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .accessibility-card p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .accessibility-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Responsive ---- */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-header-section {
      padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-lg);
    }

    .bio-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .bio-photo {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 300px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .achievements-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .priorities-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .timeline {
      padding-left: 28px;
    }

    .timeline::before {
      left: 9px;
    }

    .timeline-dot {
      left: -28px;
      width: 20px;
      height: 20px;
    }

    .timeline-dot::after {
      width: 6px;
      height: 6px;
    }

    .timeline-card {
      margin-left: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .about-comparisons {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .transparency-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .bio-photo {
      max-width: 250px;
    }

    .transparency-links a {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .timeline-item {
      opacity: 1 !important;
      animation: none !important;
    }

    .priority-static:hover .priority-static-icon {
      transform: none;
    }
  }
</style>
